pinned_questions.body: What have the artists said about the song?

body.html:
<p>Noel Gallagher on the song,</p>

<blockquote><p>I think this kind of wraps up the first part of Oasis, Which is quite innocent and pure. It started to get very serious after that, we were kind of – a big rock band although we didn’t feel it at the time.</p></blockquote>

song.markdown:
"Whatever" was released as a single after the release of [*Definitely Maybe*](http://genius.com/albums/Oasis/Definitely-maybe) and was only included as a bonus track on the Mexican edition of *Definitely Maybe*. After Oasis split up it was released to a broader audience, when included on the single compilation album *[Time Flies... 1994-2009](http://genius.com/albums/Oasis/Time-flies-19942009)*. The song is notable for its use of an orchestra. However, that was also what led to the song not being included on *Definitely Maybe*. At the time of recording the album, the band could not afford to hire an orchestra for the song.

The song came under fire for allegedly ripping off Neil Innes' song "How Sweet to Be an Idiot." They later settled a plagiarism lawsuit and Innes received a songwriting credit.

The song was often performed live, ending with the lyrics to "[Octopus's Garden](http://genius.com/The-beatles-octopuss-garden-lyrics)."
